title: OIP-21: DAO Budget Increase + Milestone Framework
body:
Summary:

Note: Current DAO budget, as approved by OIP-12, is 30k DAI/Week (in OHM equiv.).

This is a two-part actionable proposal:

    Part 1 is to authorize an additional 30k DAI/Week (60K/week total; in OHM equivalent) to support the work done by all DAO members. Please note, this budget comes from the DAO treasury ($90 million at time of writing), not the protocol treasury.

    Part 2 is to set and authorize a [framework] for two additional budget raises to 75K and 90k per week, respectively. These additional budget raises will be authorized based on key milestones (outlined below).

Abstract:

Since OIP-12, the DAO has grown from 23 to 61 active contributors (a 265% growth!). In that time and budget, the DAO delivered on multiple high-impact initiatives such as website revamp, community server onboarding revamp & Sherpa program, FOHMO 2, community education projects and strategic partnerships (Rari Fuse, Frax, AAVE, Convex, Abracadabra).

The DAO continues to operate effectively across Engineering, Marketing, Community, Partnerships, Operations and Policy teams with the current $30K/week budget. However, the latest allocation stretches some teams thin. In a recent allocation survey, 36% reported feeling underpaid. We see increased competition in the marketplace for the level of contribution we have in the DAO and we would like to retain and build on that talent. We have amazing people, we would like to pay them well, and we’d like to attract and retain the same level of talent to build together the future of Olympus.

Proposal:

Note: Allocations will continue as they have been with Strategos allocating to their department teams (marketing, partnerships, operations, policy, content, design, engineering), and project leaders allocating to their respective project teams.

Part 1 proposes an amendment to the current DAO budget, authorizing an additional 30k DAI/week (60K per week total) to be available for distribution to DAO contributors.

If passed, Part 1 will result in a total of approximately 255-265k DAI/month (in OHM equivalent) available for allocation to DAO contributors. For some comparison, $250k is equivalent to ~1.8% of RFV inflow for July, ~0.7% of DAO treasury increase for July, or ~1.5 hours of staking rewards.

Part 2 of this proposal sets a framework of milestones, which if reached, will authorize two additional budget raises to 75K and 90K/weekly, respectively.

We are proposing this [framework] for the budget because it allows a long term vision as opposed to a short term mindset; we wish to link the DAO budget to tangible milestones as set forth in this proposal.

We propose that we must accomplish at least three out of four milestones to increase the budget.

Milestones for $75k:
-15k Ohmies staking (excluding dust under 0.01 sOHM)
-17.5k Ohmies in Discord
-close 5 strategic protocol partnerships
-Launch 4 new integrations of OHM/sOHM/wsOHM

Milestones for 90K:
-17.5k Ohmies staking (excluding dust under 0.01 sOHM)
-20k Ohmies in Discord
-close 10 strategic protocol partnerships
-Launch 7 new integrations of OHM/sOHM/wsOHM

As a DAO we strive to be prudent in our spending. In an efficient organization there may occasionally be a surplus in budget, this will be rolled into the next allocation cycle.

Transparency is key. It is to be noted in this proposal; the DAO will be sharing DAO budget and allocation data on an ongoing basis each month (after monthly allocations). We will begin by sharing the current operating model, along with all allocations, up until this point in time. Here is the link to that data: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Bp0MOaD-rMXC9jWhhxCn6NmCfFpF2jlhWM-QQZ-CBUk/edit?usp=sharing

When we release the allocations for august, the sheets will also be updated with numerous charts to improve the readability of the data.

Invitation:

Any and all community members are invited to collaborate in the DAO whether it be in current projects or to propose their own project to be allocated to.

Original Forum Post: https://forum.olympusdao.finance/d/88-oip-21-dao-budget-increase-milestone-framework

Vote:
Option 1: For budget raise and framework implementation
Option 2: Against budget raise and framework implementation
